                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#3r">f. 3r</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">: Beginning of the hymn Ṭabiba ṭabibān "The Wisest
                              among the Wisest Ones".</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>: ኦእግዚኦ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ጠቢበ፡ ጠቢባን፡ ከሃሊ፡ ለአለም፡
                              እምጥንት፡ እንተ፡ ኢተበሊ…  </q> The beginning of Text I (initially missing),
                           has been written, in a secondary hand, in red and black, in the margins
                           of <locus target="#3r">3r</locus> (the same portion of text is written on
                           the added <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>
                           <note>). </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#30rb">f. 30rb</locus>
                           <desc type="GuestText">: Excerpt from a malkǝʾa-hymn for John the
                              Baptist. </desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez"> <locus target="#30rb">30rb</locus>: ሰላም፡ ለበድነ፡ ስጋከ፡
                              ዮሐንስ፡ ዜናዊ። ምጻተ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ሰርቃዊ። እምከና[...]፡ ብዕሲት፡ ካልዕት፡ ወእመሰገርት፡ ነአዊ።
                              ኦካሀን፡ ትምምክሀተ፡ ቤቱ፡ ለሌዊ፡ ለምንት፡ ሞትከ፡ እምይሙት፡ ዘማዊ። </q>
                           <note> Crudely written in green ink. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ጠቢበ፡ ጠቢባን is crudely written on the front
                           cover with yellow paint and on <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>. (here
                           written twice in blue and black pen).
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"> - The first five lines of <locus target="#3ra">3ra</locus> are framed in a square, apparently indicating that it is
                           repeated in <locus target="#2vb">2vb</locus>. 
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3"> - First nine lines of Text III-2 are written on <locus target="#30ra">30ra</locus>.
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4"> - Hardly readable note in pencil in which a date is
                           partly visible: <locus target="#32v">32v</locus>: 
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5"> - Writing excercises on <locus target="#32v">32v</locus>.
 </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6"> - Pen trials: fols.1v, 4rb.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="false">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two wooden boards (broken and repaired) covered with
                           brown tooled leather (for the most part missing); textile inlays.
                           Two pairs of sewing stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                           <material key="leather"/>
                           <material key="textile"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Small holes are visible in the centre
                           fold of the quires, close to the head and tail of the codex.
 Spine
                           protection made of parchment.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">Blind tooled ornament on the remains of the brown
                           leather cover isvisible on the front board and on the turn-ins (7 tools
                           were used: wave form, zig-zag, double line fillet, double circle, x-form,
                           criss-cross, corni-form).</decoNote>
                     </binding>
