               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0174MAKM">Māy ʾAnbasā Dabra Gannat Kidāna Mǝḥrat</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1750" notAfter="1800">Second half of the 18th century.
                        
 Quire I (<locus from="1r" to="2v">1r-2v</locus>) is of somewhat later
                        time.
 It cannot be excluded that quires II-V were originally a part of
                        a different Ms. (containing a collection of hymns? Cp. quire marks starting
                        with 11) which had been dismantled. The beginning of Text I written as
                        Additio 1 was meant to substitute for the initial portion of the text which
                        went lost. Still later (?), the same portion of the text was written on
                           <locus target="#2v">2v</locus>, a part of another added
                        bifolio.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Walātta Kidān is mentioned in supplication formulas on <locus target="#23rb">23rb</locus>, 29vb, 31rb, 31va, 32rb.</provenance>
               </history>
